  "body": "Issue Description:\r\n\r\nWhen an out-of-index blob request is made to the RPC server, the error response includes the full file path of the requested resource. This behavior could potentially expose sensitive server filesystem information to users.\r\n\r\nSteps to Reproduce:\r\n1. Execute a curl request for a blob that is out of index, using the following command:\r\n   ```\r\n   curl -H 'Accept: application/json' 'http://localhost:3500/eth/v1/beacon/blob_sidecars/$SLOT?indices=$INDEX'\r\n   ```\r\n2. Observe the error response.\r\n\r\nExpected Behavior:\r\nThe error response should not include internal file paths or any sensitive server details. It should provide a generic error message indicating the failure of the operation.\r\n\r\nActual Behavior:\r\nThe server returns an error message containing the full file path, as shown below:\r\n```\r\n{\"message\":\"Internal server error: could not retrieve blob for block root 0x... at index 4: open /Users/$USER/$DATABASE/blobs/0x.../4.ssz: no such file or directory\",\"code\":500}\r\n```\r\n\r\nImpact:\r\nExposing server file paths can lead to security vulnerabilities by providing potential attackers with insights into the server's file structure.\r\n",
